# Clean environment
rm (list = ls (all.names = TRUE)) # will clear all objects including hidden objects
gc () # free up memory and report the memory usage
options (max.print = .Machine$integer.max, scipen = 0, stringsAsFactors = F, dplyr.summarise.inform = F) # avoid truncated output in R console and keep scientific notation
setwd("~/Desktop/Lab/TRAPseq/H_EST")
# ---- Read in raw count data from text file ----
library(readr)

# Import data, skipping the first header line
featcount1_9 <- read_table(
  "./data_repository/GFP1_9.featcount.txt",
  col_names = TRUE,
  skip = 1
)
featcount10_11 <- read_table(
  "./data_repository/GFP10_11.featcount.txt",
  col_names = TRUE,
  skip = 1
)

read.count1_9 <- data.frame (featcount1_9, row.names = featcount1_9$Geneid)  # Set gene IDs as row names
#Set gene IDs as row names
read.count1_9 <- read.count1_9 [, -c(1:5)]  # Remove columns not related to gene counts
# Rename columns for consistency
orig_names <- names (read.count1_9)  # Backup original names
colnames (read.count1_9) <- c ("IT-107", "IT-108", "IT-109", "IT-110", "H-107", "H-108", "H-109", "H-110", "H-111", "UT-106", "UT-108", "UT-114", "IT-206", "IT-207", "IT-208", "IT-209", "IM-206", "IM-207", "IM-208", "IM-209", "IM-210", "UT-204", "UT-208", "UT-213", "UT-214", "UM-204", "UM-208", "UM-213", "UM-214", "UM-215")


read.count10_11 <- data.frame (featcount10_11, row.names = featcount10_11$Geneid)  # Set gene IDs as row names
#Set gene IDs as row names
read.count10_11 <- read.count10_11 [, -c(1:5)]  # Remove columns not related to gene counts
# Rename columns for consistency

    "UM-204", "UM-208", "UM-213", "UM-214", "UM-215"),
  row.names = "Sample") 

sample_info1$Groups <- as.factor (sample_info1$Groups)
all (rownames (sample_info1) %in% colnames (read.count1_9)) 
all (rownames (sample_info1) %in% colnames (read.count10_11)) 
#if "false" something is wrong
rownames(read.count1_9) <- "GFP1_9"
rownames(read.count10_11) <- "GFP10_11"

combined <- rbind(read.count1_9, read.count10_11)

df <- as.data.frame(t(combined))

df$haust_prop <- df$GFP1_9 / (df$GFP1_9 + df$GFP10_11)

library(DESeq2)

samples <- rownames(df)
condition <- gsub("-.*", "", samples)

coldata <- data.frame(condition = factor(condition), row.names = samples)

dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(
  countData = combined,
  colData = coldata,
  design = ~ condition
)
converting counts to integer mode
dds <- DESeq(dds)
estimating size factors
estimating dispersions
gene-wise dispersion estimates
mean-dispersion relationship
final dispersion estimates
fitting model and testing
res <- results(dds)

library(pheatmap)

pheatmap(
  log2(combined + 1),
  cluster_rows = FALSE,   # only 2 constructs, so no need
  cluster_cols = TRUE,    # clusters your samples
  main = "Construct Expression Across Samples",
  fontsize = 12,
  angle_col = 45
)


library(ggplot2)
ggplot(df, aes(x = GFP10_11, y = GFP1_9, color = condition)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title="Haustoriated vs Mesophyll Construct Reads",
       x="GFP1011 (Mesophyll)",
       y="GFP19 (Haustoriated)")


df <- as.data.frame(t(combined))
df$condition <- gsub("-.*", "", rownames(df))
df$haust_prop <- df$GFP1_9 / (df$GFP1_9 + df$GFP10_11)
 
pheatmap(
  as.matrix(df$haust_prop),
  cluster_rows = TRUE,
  cluster_cols = FALSE,
  labels_row = rownames(df),
  main = "Estimated Haustoriated Cell Proportion",
  fontsize = 10
)


library(ggplot2)

ggplot(df, aes(x = reorder(rownames(df), haust_prop), 
               y = haust_prop, fill = condition)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(
    title = "Haustoriated Cell Proportion per TRAP Sample",
    x = "Sample",
    y = "Haustoriated Cell Proportion"
  ) +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size = 8))


ggplot(df, aes(x = GFP10_11, y = GFP1_9, color = condition)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, linetype = "dashed") +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(
    title = "Haustoriated vs Mesophyll Construct Distribution",
    x = "GFP10-11 (Mesophyll Reads)",
    y = "GFP1-9 (Haustoriated Reads)"
  ) +
  theme(text = element_text(size = 14))

hc <- hclust(dist_matrix)

plot(
  hc,
  main = "Sample Clustering Based on Construct Counts",
  xlab = "",
  cex = 0.8
)
